title: For Sale:  Colt mational match mid-range .38 special
postcontent: Colt National Match mid range .38 special.  This is colts original kits from the early 70s built on an Essex frame.  Shoots .38 special rimmed wad cutter cartridge for a revolver. Not a .38 super conversion. Grips have gold medal from the MR Gold cup range from colt of that time. I do not know if that was part of the kit when it was supplied by colt. Kits were supplied to then famous competitors and pistol builders, Jim Clark Sr and Gil Hebard.  I do not know who built this pistol, I have scoured the internet and publications records are hard to come by for these custom built guns,  the factory colt gold cups have tracable serial numbers and came in factory boxes.  This pistol features rings in the barrels throat to delay blow back for accuracy.  It was and is a purpose built auto pistol to compete in the bullseye match to replace revolvers as the service pistol category.  The mags are 5 shot capacity.  I have 4 mags 2 of which are original Colts the other two are remanufactured. All of which are now extinct and command prices of up to $100 per mag.  I bought this from a collection arms dealer in Illinois in 2012.  I have shot it and it is amazingly accurate.  I have stocked up on wad cutter ammo as it is hard to find on the shelves.  Will sell some seperate of gun if interested at $25 a box.  I am a Delaware CCW holder if you are too we can deal in person, otherwise can meet you at XRing in Newark delaware to transfer.  Contact me to further inspect the pistol or for more pictures as I can only upload one on armslist, price is firm.

title: For Sale:  Remington 700 308 Winchester Mil-Spec
postcontent: The gun featured in this ad, is a Bolt-Action Remington 700, chambered in .308 Winchester. It is Remington’s ‘Mil-Spec’ factory rifle, as it features a stainless steel action, bolt, and heavy profiled barrel, which is 24” long, has the 5R rifling profile, 1:11.25 twist rate, and made from 416R stainless steel; all of which are features found on the true Mil-Spec M24. The action is set in an HS Precision stock that has a CNC milled full length aluminum bedding block. I received the gun BRAND NEW directly from Remington in October of 2017, as it was a replacement for a defective firearm I had purchased from them. With handloads I’ve tuned, it is truly a 1/2 MOA gun on 5 shot groups with regularity. I’m selling this gun because I simply have too many precision rifles chambered in .308 Winchester, and I want to finally build one chambered in 6.5 Creedmoor. title: For Sale:  Weimar Gew.98
postcontent: Original and matching, 1920-marked Gewehr 98 Infantry rifle...this rifle was manufactured at the DWM factory in the 1920's for issue to the Weimar Republic's Reichswehr. Having features in line with the wartime Mauser, the Weimar-era guns were sanctioned by the Treaty of Versailles as the only long arms permitted to the German military. Apart from a replacement cleaning rod and barrel band, the gun is composed of all-matching components, including the furniture and screws, and has seen no refinish or restoration. Remaining in German service during the inter-war period, this rifle would have been inherited by the Third Reich, and is typical of the weapons issued to the SA/Brownshirts, EWB, and early Waffen SS units. Having no import mark, this rifle is a fine candidate for having been brought back as a GI's war trophy. Always a scarce find for the Mauser enthusiast, examples in this condition are virtually rare, and this fine, Reichswehr-issued Gew.98 represents a strong investment as well as a superb addition to the dedicated public or private collection.
